# --- Frontend (Vercel / local) ---
#
# Primary backend — Node orchestrator in this repo (`server/`: escrow, tasks, LM, WebSocket).
# In dev, with no env vars the frontend uses http://127.0.0.1:8787 (start API: `npm run dev` at root or `npm run server:dev`).
#
# Production on Vercel — pick one approach:
#
# A) Monolith (this repo): frontend + Express from server/ as Vercel Function `api/escora`.
#    Without VITE_API_BASE_URL the browser uses the same domain (/health, /api/… via vercel.json).
#    Set Serverless Function env: DATABASE_URL, BUYER_SECRET_JSON, etc. (see server/.env.example).
#    Do not put DATABASE_URL under VITE_* — it belongs in Node only and must not leak to the client bundle.
#
# B) Separate server/ deploy + explicit URL in the frontend build:
# Vercel → VITE_API_BASE_URL = https://xxxx.up.railway.app → Redeploy.
#
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-orchestrator.example.com
# Do not use api.devnet.solana.com here — that is Solana RPC; for wallet use VITE_SOLANA_RPC_URL.
# You do not need the frontend URL in VITE_API_BASE_URL for option A (same origin works without it).
#
# SolToloka (/soltoloka): if VITE_SOLToloka_API_URL is unset — browser uses /api/soltoloka-proxy/*
# (Vercel Function). Set in project env for Functions:
# SOLTOLOKA_UPSTREAM_URL=https://soltoloka-backend.vercel.app
# Or point directly at your FastAPI:
# VITE_SOLToloka_API_URL=https://your-soltoloka.example.com
#
# CORS on the orchestrator: VITE_DEV_ORIGIN in server/.env (frontend origin).
#
# WebSocket: Vercel Serverless upgrade may not work. If needed:
# VITE_ORCHESTRATOR_WS_URL=wss://… (separate long-lived server/) or legacy:
# ORCHESTRATOR_UPSTREAM_URL + VITE_ORCHESTRATOR_VIA_PROXY=1 (/api/orchestrator-proxy for REST only).
#
# RPC for Phantom / SOL balance (default devnet)
# VITE_SOLANA_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com
#
# Wallet for dev JWT on Authorization calls (optional)
# VITE_DEPAI_DEV_WALLET=
